My bard is currently in his 16th season. I rerolled many times, mostly after some longer playing vacations (I play from old '99 days). My highest character so far was 24th necro. Mostly because I prefer role-playing to levelling. <br>
I play not more than 2-3 hours a day with some longer sessions in the weekend time. <br>
I come from Europe so my playing times could be a bit strange for US-people. But I still play with them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I'm not looking for a raiding guild, rather a pack of friends spending their time together. I love grupping and bard makes me great group-character. <br>
My desired guild should have many members in their teens and mids, not only high-enders.<br>
As to my rpg prefferences, I am agnostic so both good-neutral and evil-neutral guilds should be ok.<br>
Any ideas?<br>
